What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Fertigation and Chemigation Market?

Market Analysis and Insights

Global Fertigation and Chemigation Market

Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the fertigation and chemigation market will project a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 6.50% during the forecast period of 2022-2029 and is likely to reach the USD 47.41 billion by 2029.

The slow application of nutrients and water on or below the soil through surface drip, bubbler, subsurface drip, and micro-sprinkler systems is known as fertigation and chemigation. Fertigation and chemigation markets provide various benefits, including little water waste, minimal labor requirements, and hence the capacity to protect against drought circumstances, all of which contribute to the market's growth.

The rise of the fertigation and chemigation market is fuelled by the surging demand for quality food products. Rapid urbanization and efficiency of nutrient usage will accelerate the market’s growth. With increasing water scarcity around the world and tremendous developments and initiatives done by emerging economies through water replenishment and programmes, the fertigation and chemigation market is flourishing. Furthermore, the enhanced plant growth, yield and quality of crops will bolster the growth rate of fertigation and chemigation market. Another significant factor includes the growing water scarcity will further cushion the market’s growth rate. Other factors such as increasing population and upsurge in the demand for better quality crops will positively impact the growth rate of fertigation and chemigation market.

Moreover, strong progress in new and emerging markets will further create lucrative and remunerative growth opportunities for the fertigation and chemigation market. Additionally, government measures for the most efficient use of water resources in agriculture, as well as further assistance for the adoption of the fertigation and chemigation market in the form of subsidies, will further propel the new growth opportunities in the future year.

However, high initial investments and a lack of awareness about fertigation and chemigation will derail the fertigation and chemigation market’s growth rate. Also, enhancing efficiency and critical nutrient application doses will pose major challenges to the growth of the market. Negative impact of COVID-19 on supply chain will act as major market restrain and further hinder the growth rate of fertigation and chemigation market.

